CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 7, 1940 reads: "Concrete Proof That Courier Is Winning Its Fight - At left are pictures taken at Fort Bragg, North Carolina, where Negro soldiers are being trained for the first time in Coast Artillery technique. Top photo shows four troops inspecting anti-air-craft gun.   Bottom photo shows the type of mechanized machinery the 77th and 76th Regiments are learning how to use at Fort Bragg. Photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Five Army soldiers standing around anti-air-craft gun at Fort Bragg, North Carolina
